0UAE%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Ethiopia%20and%20Iran.%20The%20doubling%20of%20a%20group%20in%20terms%20of%20numbers%20at%20one%20stroke%20was%20unprecedented%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20had%20been%20advocating%20for%20bringing%20in%20new%20members%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20but%20the%20other%20countries%20had%20not%20displayed%20the%20same%20level%20of%20enthusiasm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20rather%20clear%20that%20India%20had%20been%20resisting%20an%20expansion%2C%20worried%20about%20the%20direction%20such%20a%20move%20would%20take.%20With%20China%20and%20then%20South%20Africa%20taking%20over%20the%20chairmanship%20in%20consecutive%20years%2C%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20was%20getting%20clearer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20was%20also%20worn%20down%20by%20the%20personal%20requests%20made%20by%20various%20countries%20who%20were%20vying%20to%20get%20in.%20While%20it%20was%20publicly%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20Iranian%20president%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-discusses-potential-expansion-of-brics-in-a-phone-call-with-iranian-president%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eengaged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20regarding%20BRICS%2C%20similar%20approaches%20were%20made%20by%20various%20other%20nations.%20The%20mounting%20diplomatic%20pressure%20was%20becoming%20untenable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJust%20ahead%20of%20the%20summit%2C%20India%20claimed%20to%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37018%2FTranscript_of_Special_Briefing_by_Foreign_Secretary_on_Prime_Ministers_visit_to_South_Africa_and_Greece_August_21_2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epositive%20intent%20and%20an%20open%20mind%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20BRICS%20expansion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110-300x109.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110-1024x372.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671137%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22436%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20logo%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20South%20Africa.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20delegations%20arrived%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20all%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20except%20one%20%E2%80%93%20were%20prepared%20with%20an%20initial%20list%20of%20candidates%20for%20membership.%20Russia%20and%20South%20Africa%20had%20a%20list%20of%20three%20countries%2C%20China%20had%20four%20and%20India%2C%20somewhat%20unexpectedly%2C%20had%20the%20largest%20with%20five%20candidates.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20surprise%20to%20see%20the%20Indians%20with%20the%20biggest%20list%20after%20all%20the%20history%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20well-informed%20official%20of%20one%20of%20the%20BRICS%20members.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20country%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20list%20of%20names%20to%20put%20forward%20was%20Brazil.%20While%20President%20Luiz%20Inacio%20Lula%20da%20Silva%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20had%20even%20talked%20about%20supporting%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fbrics-summit-brazil-idAFKBN2ZX0XO%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArgentina%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fbrazil-summit-brics-idAFS0N37802A%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVenezuela%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20diplomatic%20sources%20said%20that%20Brazilian%20officials%20did%20not%20furnish%20any%20candidates%20but%20left%20the%20final%20decision%20to%20their%20leadership.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20learnt%20that%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20initial%20list%20of%20priority%20candidates%20was%20Indonesia%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Argentina%2C%20while%20China%20had%20the%20same%20names%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20Egypt.%20India%E2%80%99s%20five%20names%20were%20those%20with%20whom%20it%20had%20a%20strategic%20partnership.%20It%20also%20included%20Indonesia%2C%20which%20withdrew%20from%20the%20race%20after%20all%20the%20members%20agreed%20to%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndonesian%20President%20Joko%20Widodo%20issued%20a%20statement%20on%20Thursday%2C%20after%20the%20expansion%20announcement%2C%20that%20Jakarta%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20in%20a%20rush%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20wanted%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexamine%E2%80%9D%20the%20membership%20issues%20further.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%2C%20however%2C%20dismissed%20speculation%20that%20Indonesia%20was%20hesitant%20due%20to%20the%20perceived%20anti-West%20agenda%20of%20the%20group%2C%20noting%20that%20President%20Widodo%20had%20seemed%20happy%20enough%20in%20South%20Africa%20when%20he%20was%20informed%20about%20the%20green%20light%20for%20Jakarta%E2%80%99s%20entry.%20The%20official%20reason%20that%20Jakarta%20provided%20the%20BRICS%20members%20is%20that%20there%20were%20some%20internal%20approvals%20and%20rules%20for%20which%20it%20needed%20some%20ASEAN%20approval.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20sources%20insisted%20that%20Indonesia%20had%20apparently%20not%20formally%20applied%20for%20membership%2C%20even%20though%20it%20was%20on%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list%20of%20candidates.%20It%20had%20apparently%20expressed%20its%20interest%20verbally%20through%20China%20earlier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20Indonesia%20withdrew%2C%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20came%20more%20sharply%20into%20the%20picture.%20China%20had%20been%20the%20strongest%20advocate%20for%20Saudi%20Arabia%20that%20also%20been%20vigorously%20lobbying%20for%20membership%2C%20but%20the%20other%20members%20felt%20that%20there%20needed%20to%20be%20a%20regional%20balance.%20Moreover%2C%20Iranian%20President%20Ebrahim%20Raisi%20had%20actively%20engaged%20in%20personal%20lobbying%20efforts%20with%20each%20member%20state%2C%20which%20made%20it%20diplomatically%20challenging%20to%20turn%20him%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Russia%20had%20strongly%20supported%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20candidacy%2C%20to%20the%20surprise%20of%20many%2C%20China%20displayed%20hesitance.%20According%20to%20well-informed%20sources%2C%20China%20even%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20necessity%20of%20expanding%20the%20group%20by%20incorporating%20numerous%20new%20entrants.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%2C%20China%20had%20a%20major%20diplomatic%20victory%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20when%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fmar%2F10%2Firan-saudi-arabia-agree-restore-ties-china-talks%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20brokered%20an%20agreement%20between%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Iran%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20restore%20diplomatic%20ties%20after%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20observers%20inferred%20from%20the%20negotiations%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20enthusiasm%20was%20somewhat%20dampened%2C%20possibly%20due%20to%20objections%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20This%20was%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Beijing%20and%20Riyadh%20having%20grown%20steadily%20closer%20in%20recent%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20appeared%20that%20the%20Saudis%20were%20also%20not%20too%20happy%20that%20the%20UAE%20was%20part%20of%20the%20new%20group.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20also%20concluded%20that%20if%20Saudi%20Arabia%20was%20brought%20into%20BRICS%2C%20Iran%20could%20be%20the%20balance%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20learnt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20one%20time%20during%20the%20negotiations%2C%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20made%20it%20almost%20seem%20like%20it%20was%20China%20versus%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20BRICS%20group%2C%20said%20a%20diplomatic%20source.%20Sensing%20the%20mood%20in%20the%20room%20and%20unwilling%20to%20be%20seen%20to%20obstruct%2C%20China%20acquiesced.%20It%20seemed%20that%20the%20candidate%20selection%20process%20was%20now%20done.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20final%20twist%20in%20the%20tale%20took%20place%20at%20the%20official%20dinner%20hosted%20by%20South%20Africa%20for%20the%20BRICS%20members%20and%20the%20other%20heads%20of%20state%20on%20the%20night%20of%20August%2023.%20Since%20the%20decision%20on%20the%20five%20countries%20had%20been%20already%20made%2C%20the%20participants%20at%20the%20dinner%20got%20an%20inkling%20of%20who%20made%20the%20cut.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20he%20learnt%20that%20his%20country%20was%20not%20on%20the%20list%2C%20Ethiopian%20Prime%20Minister%20Abiy%20Ahmed%20put%20his%20foot%20down%20during%20the%20dinner.%20He%20apparently%20conveyed%20that%20it%20was%20inconceivable%20that%20an%20African%20country%2C%20which%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccradle%20of%20humankind%E2%80%9D%20was%20not%20being%20included%20in%20the%20expanded%20BRICS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20South%20African%20president%20then%20persuaded%20the%20other%20BRICS%20member%20that%20Ethiopia%20should%20be%20included%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20on%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20sources%20confirmed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104-300x171.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104-1024x583.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671136%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEthiopian%20Prime%20Minister%20Abiy%20Ahmed%20and%20Narendra%20Modi%20during%20the%2015th%20BRICS%20Summit%20at%20Johannesburg%2C%20in%20South%20Africa%20on%20August%2024%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20criteria%20for%20becoming%20a%20BRICS%20member%20has%20not%20been%20made%20public%20so%20far%2C%20with%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20terming%20it%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37049%2FTranscript_of_Special_Briefing_by_Foreign_Secretary_on_Prime_Ministers_visit_to_South_Africa_and_Greece_August_24_2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einternal%20document%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20an%20interview%2C%20the%20South%20African%20foreign%20minister%20Naledi%20Pandor%20said%20that%20the%20criteria%20used%20in%20selecting%20the%20new%20members%20included%20commitment%20to%20progressive%20ideas%2C%20recognising%20the%20UN%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpremier%20global%20institution%E2%80%9D%2C%20belief%20in%20peace%20and%20respect%20for%20international%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20the%20BRICS%20countries%20come%20from%20backgrounds%20where%20we%20experienced%20colonialism%20and%20different%20forms%20of%20oppression%20so%20we%20believe%20in%20freedom%20and%20justice%20and%20the%20pursuit%20of%20equity%20and%20development.%20These%20are%20the%20underlying%20general%20principles%20that%20we%20elaborated%20on%20in%20the%20guideline%20document%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeslive.co.za%2Fsunday-times%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023-08-27-naledi-pandor-outlines-criteria-needed-to-become-a-member-of-brics%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshe%20said%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%20said%20that%20while%20these%20are%20the%20ideals%20that%20news%20members%20would%20agree%20with%2C%20there%20were%20also%20economic%20parameters%20that%20were%20drawn%20up.%20These%20included%20limits%20like%20trade%20with%20BRICS%20members%20at%20around%20%2450%20billion%20or%20a%20GDP%20of%20around%20%24400%20billion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20it%20was%20stressed%20that%20these%20were%20just%20general%20parameters.%20%E2%80%9CPotential%20members%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20meet%20all%20these%20economic%20criteria%2C%E2%80%9D%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693634517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24001805%2FF4NKlFIWcAAT_Qt.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-expansion-inside-story%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20the%20delegations%20arrived%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20all%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20except%20one%20%E2%80%93%20were%20prepared%20with%20an%20initial%20list%20of%20candidates%20for%20membership.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%2