inery%2C%20was%20first%20put%20to%20use%20by%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20as%20a%20swift%20justice%20dispensation.%20It%20was%20touted%20as%20a%20mechanism%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwatch-how-yogi-perfected-bulldozer-justice-bjps-new-weapon-against-muslims%5C%22%3Egood%20and%20effective%20governance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20harshest%20ways%20to%20punish%20not%20only%20the%20alleged%20perpetrators%20of%20crimes%20but%20also%20their%20families.%20This%20form%20of%20punishment%20treads%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20state-sanctioned%20collective%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20established%20principles%20of%20criminal%20jurisprudence%20is%20that%20the%20punishment%20must%20be%20objective%20and%20proportionate%20to%20the%20crime.%20Besides%2C%20only%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Felibrary.law.psu.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1571%26context%3Dpsilr%5C%22%3Eperpetrator%20of%20a%20crime%20is%20to%20be%20solely%20punished%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20specific%20offence%20under%20which%20they%20are%20charged.%20However%2C%20when%20a%20house%20is%20demolished%20due%20to%20the%20illegal%20activities%20of%20one%20of%20its%20inhabitants%2C%20all%20the%20other%20residents%20bear%20the%20repercussions%20of%20those%20actions.%20This%20practice%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98collective%20punishment%E2%80%99%20and%20is%20frequently%20employed%20in%20Israel%20against%20Palestinians%2C%20who%20constitute%20a%20minority%20within%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20houses%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20have%20been%20demolished%20over%20the%20years.%20The%20Israeli%20government%20relies%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.btselem.org%2Fpunitive_demolitions%2Fregulation_119%5C%22%3EBritish-era%20Regulation%20119%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20states%20that%20the%20Military%20Commander%20can%20allow%20forfeiture%20of%20any%20house%20or%20land%20where%20any%20person%20who%20has%20committed%20a%20crime%20or%20attempted%20to%20commit%20a%20crime%20lives.%20They%20can%20either%20demolish%20the%20house%20or%20any%20part%20or%20structure%20of%20the%20house.%20These%20and%20other%20British%20regulations%20were%20terminated%20prior%20to%20the%20end%20of%20their%20mandate%20by%20the%20Palestine%20(Revocations)%20Order-in-Council%20of%201948.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Israel%20argues%20that%20the%20revocation%20order%20was%20not%20published%20in%20the%20official%20Palestinian%20Gazette%2C%20thus%2C%20it%20was%20not%20revoked.%20The%20Israeli%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20petitioned%20on%20various%20occasions%20regarding%20the%20demolition%20of%20houses%20but%20the%20court%20has%20always%20restricted%20itself%20to%20adjudicating%20the%20legality%20of%20such%20actions%20under%20Regulation%20119.%20The%20apex%20court%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fheinonline.org%2FHOL%2FPage%3Fhandle%3Dhein.journals%2Fpsilr21%26div%3D36%26g_sent%3D1%26casa_token%3DjLDKGomv2RwAAAAA%3AD606eekeHq1_niQRKGZDqhULA9_UgI8NdwEf3uV7IXq4uQ5LT512_z0X-_J2xNV5G6iX8lSxvA%26collection%3Djournals%5C%22%3Enoted%20that%20these%20actions%20violate%20international%20principles%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20has%20never%20held%20this%20to%20be%20an%20act%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20punishment%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20in%20a%20case%20held%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20basis%20to%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20complaint%20that%20house%20demolition%20is%20a%20form%20of%20collective%20punishment.%20In%20their%20opinion%2C%20only%20the%20terrorists%20and%20criminals%20themselves%20should%20be%20punished%2C%20and%20house%20demolition%20punishes%20additional%20family%20members%20who%20will%20be%20left%20without%20shelter.%20Such%20an%20interpretation%2C%20if%20accepted%20by%20us%2C%20would%20leave%20the%20above%20Regulation%20and%20its%20orders%20void%20of%20content%2C%20leaving%20only%20the%20possibility%20of%20punishing%20a%20terrorist%20who%20lives%20alone.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20case%20before%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20terrorists%20came%20from%20certain%20homes%2C%20and%20these%20homes%20%E2%80%93%20and%20no%20others%20%E2%80%93%20are%20about%20to%20be%20demolished.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpunishment%E2%80%9D%20has%20not%20been%20imposed%20on%20the%20homes%20of%20uninvolved%20persons%2C%20and%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20understand%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20claim%20that%20we%20are%20here%20dealing%20with%20a%20case%20of%20collective%20punishment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20case%2C%20the%20court%20noted%20the%20hardship%20put%20on%20the%20family%20but%20said%20that%20achieving%20the%20ends%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdeterrence%E2%80%9D%20was%20justified.%20But%20the%20Justice%20refused%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20hardship%20on%20a%20family%20due%20to%20the%20demolition%20of%20a%20house%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20punishment%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDemolishing%20%E2%80%98illegally%E2%80%99%20constructed%20houses%3A%20A%20procedural%20anomaly%20in%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20we%20presume%20that%20the%20houses%20were%20constructed%20illegally%2C%20civic%20authorities%20must%20still%20adhere%20to%20the%20standard%20procedures%20before%20and%20during%20the%20demolition%20process.%20Although%20the%20rules%20might%20vary%20from%20state%20to%20state%2C%20the%20municipal%20corporation%20is%20required%20to%20serve%20a%20notice%20before%20demolishing%20someone%E2%80%99s%20property.%20It%20would%20be%20relevant%20to%20mention%20some%20of%20the%20pertinent%20legislation%20to%20illustrate%20how%20they%20were%20blatantly%20disregarded%20or%20how%20authorities%20merely%20paid%20lip%20service%20to%20them%2C%20thus%20demonstrating%20their%20lack%20of%20genuine%20adherence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F10587%2F1%2FAthe_uttar_pradesh_urban_planning_and_development_act%252C_1973.pdf%5C%22%3EUttar%20Pradesh%20Urban%20Planning%20and%20Development%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20section%2027%20(1)%20says%20that%20if%20any%20development%20has%20been%20carried%20out%20without%20prior%20approval%2C%20the%20same%20should%20be%20removed%20between%2015-40%20days%20from%20the%20day%20on%20which%20the%20copy%20of%20the%20order%20was%20issued.%20Further%2C%20it%20also%20provides%20an%20opportunity%20to%20the%20person%20to%20appeal%20the%20said%20order%20to%20the%20chairman%20within%2030%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmptownplan.nic.in%2FRules%2Fvikasniyam%2FMPBVN-1984.pdf%5C%22%3EMP%20Bhumi%20Vikas%20Rules%201984%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ten%20days%20are%20provided%20to%20the%20violator%20to%20stop%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20Act.%20Similarly%2C%20section%20343%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F1410%2F1%2Fa1957-66.pdf%5C%22%3EDelhi%20Municipal%20Corporation%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201957%20requires%20that%20a%20notice%20should%20be%20served%20to%20the%20person%20before%20carrying%20out%20demolition%20and%20the%20property%20occupant%20must%20be%20given%20five%20to%2015%20days%20before%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20structure.%20Further%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98reasonable%20opportunity%E2%80%99%20should%20be%20provided%20to%20clarify%20why%20this%20action%20should%20not%20be%20undertaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbareactslive.com%2FHRY%2Fhl479.htm%5C%22%3EHaryana%20Municipal%20Corporation%20Act%2C%201944%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20requires%20a%20show%20cause%20notice%20to%20be%20served%20to%20the%20person%20as%20to%20why%20the%20demolition%20should%20not%20take%20place.%20Section%20261%20also%20prescribes%20a%20three-day%20notice%20period%20to%20be%20served.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20discussion%20of%20certain%20recent%20incidences%20of%20demolition%20shall%20demonstrate%20how%20the%20procedures%20were%20either%20violated%20or%20circumvented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecent%20incidents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20house%20of%20a%20Muslim%20family%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmuslim-man-house-demolished-ujjain-viral-video%5C%22%3Edemolished%20with%20drums%20and%20dhol%20playing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20the%20allegations%20that%20two%20juveniles%20and%20an%2018-year-old%20spat%20on%20a%20Hindu%20religious%20procession.%20Before%20that%2C%20in%20January%2C%20the%20houses%20of%20two%20businessmen%2C%20belonging%20to%20a%20Hindu%20and%20a%20Muslim%20family%2C%20were%20demolished%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmadhya-pradesh-chinese-manjha-house-demolished%5C%22%3Eselling%20%E2%80%9CChinese%20%3Cem%3Emanjha%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20UP%20government%20arrested%20and%20then%20demolished%20the%20house%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fdemolition-completely-illegal-compensation-must-be-paid-former-allahabad-hc-chief-justice%5C%22%3EJaved%20Muhammed%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20briefly%20arresting%20a%20family%20member.%20They%20were%20served%20only%20a%20day%E2%80%99s%20notice%20to%20take%20their%20belongings%20from%20the%20house.%20Further%2C%20as%20per%20the%20family%2C%20the%20house%20was%20not%20even%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Muhammed%2C%20it%20was%20in%20the%20name%20of%20his%20wife%20and%20the%20demolition%20order%20did%20not%20even%20have%20her%20name%20on%20it.%20The%20notice%20was%20pasted%20on%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20house%20one%20day%20prior%20to%20it%20being%20demolished%20and%20was%20backdated.%20It%20also%20mentions%20certain%20hearings%20that%20the%20family%20had%20no%20idea%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20a%20drive%20was%20carried%20out%20in%20Kanpur%2C%20during%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20emphasised%20that%20house%20demolitions%20should%20not%20be%20conducted%20as%20acts%20of%20retaliation%20and%20stressed%20the%20importance%20of%20adhering%20to%20proper%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHundreds%20of%20incidents%20have%20also%20been%20reported%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Assam%2C%20and%20Gujarat%2C%20and%20the%20target%20community%20has%20always%20remained%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20after%20the%20Nuh%20violence%2C%20750%20houses%20and%20shops%20belonging%20to%20the%20Muslim%20community%20were%20demolished.%20In%20some%20case%2C%20no%20prior%20notice%20was%20issued%2C%20while%20in%20others%20only%20a%20half%20an%20hour%20notice%20was%20issued%20before%20the%20demolition.%20Many%20were%20not%20able%20to%20take%20their%20belongings%20before%20their%20houses%20were%20demolished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20residents%20claimed%20that%20the%20houses%20were%20built%20legally.%20Even%20though%20just%20a%20day%20after%20the%20officials%20said%20that%20the%20demolitions%20were%20not%20linked%20to%20the%20protests%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharyana-for-the-third-day-authorities-demolish-dozens-of-shops-in-violence-hit-nuh%5C%22%3ESDM%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20these%20demolitions%20were%20linked%20to%20the%20protest.%20The%20state%20home%20minister%20had%20also%20said%20that%20the%20government%20would%20use%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbulldozer%E2%80%9D%20if%20the%20need%20arises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20High%20Court%20took%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fpunjab-haryana-high-court-asks-on-nuh-demolition-drive-whether-buildings-belonging-to-particular-community-brought-down-as-exercise-of-ethnic-cleansing-234623%5C%22%3Esuo%20motu%20cognisance%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20case%20and%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CApparently%2C%20without%20any%20demolition%20orders%20and%20notices%2C%20the%20law%20and%20order%20problem%20is%20being%20used%20as%20a%20ruse%20to%20bring%20down%20buildings%20without%20following%20the%20procedure%20established%20by%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20raised%20the%20question%20whether%20it%20was%20an%20attempt%20at%20%E2%80%9Cethnic%20cleansing%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20a%20demolition%20operation%20took%20place%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Jahangirpuri%20after%20incidents%20of%20violence%20were%20reported%20during%20a%20religious%20procession%20on%20Hanuman%20Jayanti.%20It%20was%20alleged%20that%20the%20rioters%20had%20constructed%20%E2%80%98illegal%20buildings%E2%80%99%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20demolished.%20Two%20petitions%20were%20filed%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20opposition%20to%20these%20demolitions%2C%20and%20the%20court%20issued%20an%20order%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo.%20However%2C%20despite%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20directive%2C%20the%20demolitions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjahangirpuri-after-bulldozers-arrive-sc-orders-status-quo-on-anti-encroachment-drive%5C%22%3Econtinued%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20approximately%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20United%20Nations%20Special%20Rapporteurs%20%E2%80%93%20for%20Housing%2C%20Minority%20Issues%20and%20Freedom%20of%20Religion%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fun-special-rapporteurs-condemn-home-demolitions-in-india-see-collective-punishment-of-muslims%5C%22%3Ehad%20written%20a%20joint%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Indian%20government%20strongly%20criticising%20and%20protesting%20arbitrary%20demolitions%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Khargone%2C%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Anand%20and%20Delhi%20Jahangirpuri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20is%20enough%20to%20show%20that%20these%20actions%20are%20taken%20against%20rioters%20in%20the%20name%20of%20unauthorised%20structures.%20This%20suggests%20that%20these%20actions%20are%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Flead%2Fdemolitions-as-state-sanctioned-collective-punishment%2Farticle67180107.ece%5C%22%3Estate-sanctioned%20collective%20punishment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20if%20the%20rioters%20are%20to%20be%20punished%2C%20instead%20of%20following%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%2C%20the%20states%20have%20started%20to%20demolish%20their%20houses%20and%20have%20seemed%20to%20have%20forgotten%20the%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%98innocent%20until%20proven%20guilty%E2%80%99%20enshrined%20under%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20Their%20entire%20families%20are%20made%20to%20suffer%20for%20the%20sole%20acts%20of%20one%20or%20two%20members%20of%20the%20family.%20Further%2C%20it%20should%20be%20noted%20that%20in%20Nuh%2C%20the%20houses%20of%20people%20belonging%20to%20only%20one%20community%20were%20demolished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20actions%20clearly%20infringe%20upon%20constitutional%20rights%20and%20disregard%20fundamental%20principles%2C%20such%20as%20the%20presumption%20of%20innocence%20until%20proven%20guilty.%20Moreover%2C%20these%20also%20go%20against%20the%20constitutional%20interpretations%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Life%2C%20as%20articulated%20in%20landmark%20Supreme%20Court%20judgments%20like%3Cem%3E%20Olga%20Tellis%20v.%20Bombay%20Municipal%20Corporation%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdemolition-anti-encroachment-drives-what-does-the-law-say%5C%22%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20affirmed%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20under%20Article%2021%20encompasses%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20entitlement%20to%20live%20with%20dignity%2C%20access%20to%20housing%2C%20and%20the%20means%20of%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdemolition-livelihood-wreck-punitive-measure-hlrn-report%5C%22%3EHousing%20and%20Land%20Rights%20Initiative%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20158%20incidents%20of%20house%20demolitions%2Fforced%20evictions%20have%20taken%20place%20in%202021%20alone.%20Further%2C%20between%20January%20to%20July%202022%2C%2025%2C800%20homes%20across%20the%20country%20were%20demolished.%20For%20many%20of%20these%20instances%2C%20the%20demolitions%20took%20place%20to%20punish%20the%20alleged%20rioters%20after%20communal%20clashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20pattern%20has%20been%20witnessed%20in%20the%20house%20demolitions%20by%20the%20Israeli%20government%2C%20where%20in%202022%2C%20houses%20of%20approximately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeastmonitor.com%2F20221229-report-israel-demolished-950-palestinian-homes-in-2022%2F%5C%22%3E950%20Palestinians%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20demolished.%20This%20shows%20that%20these%20actions%20are%20not%20only%20restricted%20to%20merely%20removing%20illegal%20structures%20but%20to%20set%20an%20example%20and%20punish%20not%20only%20the%20alleged%20perpetrator%20of%20a%20crime%20but%20their%20entire%20family%2C%20making%20it%20a%20form%20of%20%E2%80%98collective%20punishment%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmrashaa%20is%20a%20researcher%20based%20out%20of%20Mumbai.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EAmit%20Kumar%20has%20been%20a%20fellow%20with%20the%20Max%20Planck%20Institute%20of%20Social%20Law%20and%20Social%20Policy%20and%20is%20currently%20an%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Law%2C%20Maharashtra%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Mumbai.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20views%20expressed%20by%20authors%20are%20purely%20personal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693566058000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F27142325%2F2022_4img26_Apr_2022_PTI04_26_2022_000186B-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdemolitions-as-tools-of-collective-punishment-examining-instances-in-india-and-israel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20a%20house%20is%20demolished%20due%20to%20the%20illegal%20activities%20of%20one%20of%20its%20inhabitants%2C%20all%20the%20other%20residents%20bear%20t