crossfire%20between%20two%20communities%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Border%20Security%20Forces%20jawan%20Ranjit%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20family%20still%20awaits%20any%20compensation%20from%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConstable%20Ranjit%20Yadav%2C%20who%20was%20posted%20with%20the%20163%20Battalion%2C%20was%20the%20lone%20breadwinner%20in%20his%20eight-member%20family%2C%20residing%20in%20Kankinara%20of%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20North%2024%20Parganas%20district.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKaushalya%20Yadav%20(34)%2C%20his%20widow%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CRanjit%20left%20home%20saying%20that%20we%20will%20find%20a%20suitable%20boy%20as%20groom%20for%20his%20younger%20sister%2C%20once%20he%20is%20back.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20he%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20his%20promise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20past%20four%20months%2C%20violence%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20northeastern%20state%20of%20Manipur%20has%20raged%20between%20the%20Meitei%20and%20Kuki%20communities%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20loss%20of%20over%20160%20lives%2C%20including%20that%20of%20Ranjit%20Yadav.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKaushalya%20had%20approached%20the%20Manipur%20government%20twice%20for%20compensation.%20But%20says%20that%20she%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20received%20any%20money%2C%20from%20either%20the%20state%20government%20or%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20yet.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERanjit%20was%20deployed%20in%20the%20state%20since%20May%203%2C%20when%20violence%20broke%20out.%20On%20the%20night%20of%20June%205%2C%20he%20spoke%20to%20Kaushalya%20over%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20June%206%2C%20Ranjit%20sustained%20a%20bullet%20injury%20near%20his%20chest%20and%20was%20rushed%20to%20the%20Jitan%20Hospital%20in%20Kakching%20where%20he%20was%20declared%20dead.%20A%20BSF%20official%20said%20suspected%20Kuki%20miscreants%20resorted%20to%20indiscriminate%20and%20heavy%20firing%20targeted%20at%20BSF%20troops%20deployed%20at%20the%20Serou%20Practical%20High%20School.%20Two%20soldiers%20from%20Assam%20Rifles%20were%20also%20injured%20on%20the%20same%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERanjit%E2%80%99s%20body%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20family%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20i.e.%2C%20June%206.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20told%20our%2011-year-old%20that%20his%20father%20will%20never%20come%20back.%20The%20truth%20will%20make%20him%20strong%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kaushalya%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAayush%2C%20Ranjit%20and%20Kaushalya%E2%80%99s%20son%20had%20in%20fact%20been%20skipping%20school%20out%20of%20the%20belief%20that%20his%20father%20might%20return%20any%20moment.%20He%20has%20returned%20to%20school%20now%20and%20wants%20to%20join%20the%20Indian%20Army.%20His%20mother%20said%20that%20his%20new%20dream%20is%20to%20replace%20his%20father%20in%20the%20position%20and%20fight%20for%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20urged%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20communities%20to%20resume%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYadav%20had%20two%20sisters%20%E2%80%93%20Buli%20(21)%20and%20Urmila%20(32).%20Buli%20is%20visually%20impaired.%20In%20addition%20to%20them%20and%20his%20wife%20and%20child%2C%20he%20also%20had%20a%20brother%2C%20Sanjeet%20(26)%20and%20his%20elderly%20parents%20who%20were%20dependent%20on%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20these%20times%20of%20inflation%20were%20even%20one%20person%20cannot%20survive%2C%20I%20have%20to%20earn%20for%20seven%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kaushalya%2C%20who%20adds%20that%20even%20the%20West%20Bengal%20government%20has%20not%20done%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaushalya%2C%20who%20is%20a%20Class%2010%20graduate%2C%20is%20looking%20for%20jobs.%20Many%20politicians%20have%20visited%20the%20family%2C%20she%20noted.%20However%2C%20for%20everyday%20expenses%20Kaushalya%20has%20had%20to%20borrow%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnion%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20in%20his%20press%20conference%20on%20June%201%2C%20had%20promised%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20as%20compensation%20to%20the%20kin%20of%20those%20who%20died%20in%20the%20violence.%20Data%20received%20from%20District%20Collector%E2%80%99s%20office%20Kakching%20shows%20that%20six%20people%20have%20got%20Rs%205%20lakh%20as%20compensation%20(the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20share).%20However%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20name%20was%20not%20in%20the%20list%20when%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20checked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693558828000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01140506%2FUntitled-design-13.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmanipur-bsf-jawan-compensation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Constable%20Ranjit%20Yadav%2C%20who%20was%20posted%20with%20the%20163%20Battalion%2C%20was%20the%20lone%20breadwinner%20in%20his%20eight-member%20family%2C%20residing%20in%20Kankinara%20of%20West%20Bengal's%20North%2024%20Parganas%20district.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmanipur-bsf-jawan-compensation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Madras%20HC%20Pulls%20Up%20TN%20Anti-Corruption%20Watchdog%20for%20'Changing%20Stance'%20as%20Per%20Party%20in%20Power%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2FMadras_High_Court_PTI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Madras%20high%20court%20has%20come%20down%20heavily%20on%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Vigilance%20and%20Anti-corruption%20(DVAC)%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%20changing%20colours%20depending%20on%20which%20political%20party%20is%20in%20power%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fdvac-has-become-a-chameleon-says-madras-hc-as-it-takes-suo-motu-revision-of-ops-case-2667894%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20made%20the%20comments%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2031%2C%20after%20deciding%20to%20take%20suo%20motu%20revision%20of%20a%202012%20local%20court%20order%20that%20had%20permitted%20DVAC%20to%20withdraw%20a%20disproportionate%20assets%20(DA)%20case%20against%20former%20chief%20minister%20O.%20Panneerselvam%2C%20a%20year%20after%20his%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AIADMK)%20party%20came%20to%20power%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Anand%20Venkatesh%20has%20also%20decided%20to%20review%20the%20local%20court%20order%20of%202012%20which%20had%20also%20discharged%20three%20Dravid%20Muuentra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20ministers%20K.%20Ponmudy%2C%20K.K.%20S.S.R.%20Ramachandran%2C%20and%20Thangam%20Thennarasu%20from%20disproportionate%20asset%20cases%20along%20with%20Pannerselvam.%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20anti-corruption%20watchdog%2C%20DVAC%2C%20had%20filed%20the%20case%20against%20Pannerselvam%20in%202006%2C%20and%20the%20charge%20sheet%20in%20the%20case%20was%20filed%20in%202009%20after%20the%20DMK%20came%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20DVAC%20has%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%2C%20Justice%20Venkatesh%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%2C%20courts%20have%20also%20acted%20in%20tandem%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20court%20will%20be%20failing%20in%20its%20constitutional%20duty%20if%20it%20%E2%80%9Ccloses%20its%20eyes%20to%20such%20systemic%20failure%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20fourth%20time%20in%20a%20month%20that%20the%20high%20court%20has%20pulled%20up%20DVAC.%20Last%20week%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20is%20very%20rotten%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Special%20Court%20for%20MP%2FMLA%20Cases%20at%20Sriviliputhur%2C%20while%20taking%20up%20suo%20motu%20revision%20of%20cases%20involving%20Ramachandran%20and%20Thennarasu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20down%20heavily%20on%20the%20DVAC%20officials%2C%20the%20judge%20observed%20that%20they%20had%20changed%20their%20stance%20after%202021%2C%20the%20year%20when%20the%20DMK%20assumed%20power%20after%20defeating%20AIADMK%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693557047000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2FMadras_High_Court_PTI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmadras-hc-pulls-up-tn-anti-corruption-watchdog-for-changing-stance-as-per-party-in-power%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20described%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Vigilance%20and%20Anti-corruption%20a%20'chameleon'%20changing%20colours%20to%20suit%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20governing%20party.%20It%20made%20the%20remarks%20after%20deciding%20to%20review%20a%202012%20local%20court%20order%20which%20withdrew%20a%20disproportionate%20assets%20case%20against%20former%20CM%20Pannerselvam.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmadras-hc-pulls-up-tn-anti-corruption-watchdog-for-changing-stance-as-per-party-in-power%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Legionnaires'%20disease%20has%20killed%2016%20people%20in%20Poland%20and%20been%20found%20on%20the%20asylum%20seeker%20barge%20-%20but%20what%20is%20it%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693556820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-legionnaires-disease_6262328.jpg%3F20230825143239%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Flegionnaires-disease-has-killed-16-people-in-poland-and-been-found-on-the-asylum-seeker-barge-but-what-is-it-12952054%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bacteria%20that%20causes%20Legionnaires'%20disease%20has%20been%20found%20in%20Poland%20near%20the%20Ukrainian%20border%20and%20on%20the%20barge%20due%20to%20house%20asylum%20seekers%20in%20Dorset.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Flegionnaires-disease-has-killed-16-people-in-poland-and-been-found-on-the-asylum-seeker-barge-but-what-is-it-12952054%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Flegionnaires-disease-has-killed-16-people-in-poland-and-been-found-on-the-asylum-seeker-barge-but-what-is-it-12952054%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Flegionnaires-disease-has-killed-16-people-in-poland-and-been-found-on-the-asylum-seeker-barge-but-what-is-it-12952054%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commission%20Appointments%3A%20It%E2%80%99s%20Time%20to%20Go%20Back%20to%20the%20Future%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%2073-year%20journey%20as%20a%20constitutionally%20mandated%20body%20in%20charge%20of%20conducting%20elections%20to%20Parliament%2C%20state%20assemblies%2C%20and%20the%20position%20of%20president%20and%20vice-president%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20has%20had%20its%20ups%20and%20downs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20two%20election%20commissioners%20(EC)%20have%20traditionally%20been%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20acting%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20%E2%80%93%20effectively%20by%20the%20union%20government%2C%20or%20the%20executive%20%E2%80%93%20the%20core%20concern%20regarding%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20performance%20has%20always%20been%20that%20of%20its%20independence%20%E2%80%93%20how%20independent%20is%20it%20to%20conduct%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20a%20crucial%20aspect%20of%20a%20functioning%20and%20resilient%20democracy.%20What%20impact%20if%20any%20does%20a%20government%20with%20a%20brute%20majority%20in%20parliament%20have%20on%20the%20independent%20working%20of%20the%20institution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20question%2C%20which%20has%20resounded%20across%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape%20in%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20creating%20a%20sense%20of%20disquiet%2C%20has%20gathered%20storm%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months.%20After%20all%2C%20there%20is%20a%20line-up%20of%20state%20assembly%20elections%20before%20the%20nation%20goes%20to%20the%20polls%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20on%20March%202%2C%202023%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2015%2F1458%2F1458_2015_3_1501_42634_Judgement_02-Mar-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAnoop%20Baranwal%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20directed%20that%20the%20appointments%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20done%20by%20the%20President%20of%20India%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20advice%20tendered%20by%20a%20Committee%20consisting%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%2C%20in%20case%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20Leader%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20largest%20Party%20in%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20having%20the%20largest%20numerical%20strength%2C%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%20This%20norm%20will%20continue%20to%20hold%20good%20till%20a%20law%20is%20made%20by%20the%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2010%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FBill_Text_Chief_Election_Commissioner_and_other_Election_Commissioners_Bill_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Terms%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20saying%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20President%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20Selection%20Committee%20consisting%20of%E2%80%94%20(a)%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%94Chairperson%3B%20(b)%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%E2%80%94Member%3B%20(c)%20a%20Union%20Cabinet%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%94Member.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20sequence%20of%20events%20has%20fuelled%20an%20animated%20debate%20among%20legal%20scholars%2C%20former%20CECs%2C%20civil%20servants%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%20in%20the%20public%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20clear%2C%20unambiguous%20assessment%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20judgment%20would%20help%20foreground%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20issue%20at%20stake%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20appointments%20to%20the%20ECI%20are%20so%20crucial%20that%20we%20need%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20and%20the%20Bill%20for%20a%20fresh%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221156%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01-300x187.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01-1024x638.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671125%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Central%20Wing%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%20where%20the%20Chief%20Justice%E2%80%99s%20courtroom%20is%20situated.%20Photo%3A%20Subhashish%20Panigrahi%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudgments%20of%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20typically%20comprise%20several%20major%20segments.%20They%20begin%20with%20what%20can%20broadly%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20case%20%E2%80%93%20the%20historical%20or%20contextual%20background%2C%20a%20summary%20of%20relevant%20laws%20including%20those%20presented%20by%20the%20opposing%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20come%20the%20critical%20components%2C%20sometimes%20partly%20overlapping%20with%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20case%2C%20namely%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Edirection(s)%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Eratio%20decidendi%20(%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20legal%20principle%20or%20rationale%20for%20the%20decision)%2C%20which%20are%20essential.%20(The%20other%20component%2C%20%3Cem%3Eobiter%20dicta%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20that%20which%20is%20said%20in%20passing%20by%20the%20judge%2C%20is%20not%20essential%20to%20the%20ruling.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0rationale%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%2C%20reproduced%20above%2C%20is%20excerpted%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3Epara%20125%20of%20Justice%20Ajay%20Rastogi%E2%80%99s%20concurring%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CKeeping%20in%20view%20the%20importance%20of%20maintaining%20the%20neutrality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20hold%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20which%20is%20a%20sine%20qua%20non%20for%20upholding%20the%20democracy%20as%20enshrined%20in%20our%20Constitution%2C%20it%20becomes%20imperative%20to%20shield%20the%20appointment%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20to%20be%20insulated%20from%20the%20executive%20interference%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0In%20the%20main%20judgment%2C%20Justice%20K.M.%20Joseph%2C%20speaking%20for%20himself%2C%20Justice%20Aniruddha%20Bose%2C%20Justice%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%2C%20and%20Justice%20C.T.%20Ravikumar%2C%20writes%20a%20separate%20section%20titled%20%E2%80%98Independence%3A%20a%20sterling%20and%20indispensable%20attribute.%E2%80%99%20This%20section%2C%20which%20forms%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20entire%20judgment%2C%20deserves%20to%20be%20quoted%20at%20some%20length%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20independence%3F%20Independence%20is%20a%20value%2C%20which%20is%20only%20one%20of%20the%20elements%20in%20the%20amalgam%20of%20virtues%20that%20a%20person%20should%20possess.%20The%20competence%20of%20a%20man%20is%20not%20to%20be%20conflated%20with%20fierce%20independence.%20A%20person%20may%20be%20excellent%2C%20i.e.%2C%20at%20his%20chosen%20vocation.%20He%20may%20be%20an%20excellent%20Administrator.%20He%20may%20be%20honest%20but%20the%20quality%20of%20independence%20transcends%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20qualities%20of%20professional%20excellence%2C%20as%20also%20the%20dictates%20of%20honesty.%20We%20may%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20clarify%20that%2C%20ordinarily%2C%20honesty%20would%20embrace%20the%20quality%20of%20courage%20of%20conviction%2C%20flowing%20from%20the%20perception%20of%20what%20is%20right%20and%20what%20is%20wrong.%20%3Cem%3EIrrespective%20of%20consequences%20to%20the%20individual%2C%20an%20honest%20person%20would%2C%20ordinarily%2C%20unrelentingly%20take%20on%20the%20high%20and%20mighty%20and%20persevere%20in%20the%20righteous%20path.%20An%20Election%20Commissioner%20is%20answerable%20to%20the%20Nation.%20The%20people%20of%20the%20country%20look%20forward%20to%20him%20so%20that%20democracy%20is%20always%20preserved%20and%20fostered.%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Independence%20must%20be%20related%2C%20finally%2C%20to%20the%20question%20of%20%E2%80%98what%20is%20right%20and%20what%20is%20wrong%E2%80%99.%20A%20person%2C%20who%20is%20weak%20kneed%20before%20the%20powers%20that%20be%2C%20cannot%20be%20appointed%20as%20an%20Election%20Commissioner.%20A%20person%2C%20who%20is%20in%20a%20state%20of%20obligation%20or%20feels%20indebted%20to%20the%20one%20who%20appointed%20him%2C%20fails%20the%20nation%20and%20can%20have%20no%20place%20in%20the%20conduct%20of%20elections%2C%20forming%20the%20very%20foundation%20of%20the%20democracy.%20An%20independent%20person%20cannot%20be%20biased.%20Holding%20the%20scales%20evenly%2C%20even%20in%20the%20stormiest%20of%20times%2C%20not%20being%20servile%20to%20the%20powerful%2C%20but%20coming%20to%20the%20rescue%20of%20the%20weak%20and%20the%20wronged%2C%20who%20are%20otherwise%20in%20the%20right%2C%20would%20qualify%20as%20true%20independence.%20Upholding%20the%20constitutional%20values%2C%20which%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Basic%20Structure%2C%20and%20which%20includes%2C%20democracy%2C%20the%20Rule%20of%20Law%2C%20the%20Right%20to%20Equality%2C%20secularism%20and%20the%20purity%20of%20elections%E2%80%A6%20would%2C%20indeed%2C%20proclaim%20the%20presence%20of%20independence.%20Independence%20must%20embrace%20the%20ability%20to%20be%20firm%2C%20even%20as%20against%20the%20highest%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Not%20unnaturally%2C%20uncompromising%20fearlessness%20will%20mark%20an%20independent%20person%20from%20those%20who%20put%20all%20they%20hold%20dear%20before%20their%20Karma.%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20important%20that%20the%20appointment%20must%20not%20be%20overshadowed%20by%20even%20a%20perception%2C%20that%20a%20%E2%80%98yes%20man%E2%80%99%20will%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20democracy%20and%20all%20that%20it%20promises%20%3C%2Fem%3E(emphasis%20added)%3Cem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20essence%20of%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20decision%20of%20this%20judgment%2C%20therefore%20is%20independence%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20their%20insulation%20from%20executive%20interference.%20Independence%2C%20in%20this%20context%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmust%20embrace%20the%20ability%20to%20be%20firm%2C%20even%20as%20%5Bsic%5D%20against%20the%20highest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Watch%20%7C%20'Modi%20Govt's%20EC%20Bill%20Undermines%20Its%20Independence%2C%20Should%20Be%20Struck%20Down%20if%20Passed'%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-election-commission-gautam-bhatia%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Modi%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20EC%20Bill%20Undermines%20Its%20Independence%2C%20Should%20Be%20Struck%20Down%20if%20Passed%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20far%20does%20the%20Bill%20follow%20the%20rationale%20of%20SC%20ruling%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20%3C%2Fem%3Equick%20look%20at%20the%20table%20below%20is%20sufficient%20to%20show%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20The%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Terms%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20follows%20the%20rationale%20anchoring%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3ESection%20No.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EDescription%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3ESupports%20independence%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3EReduces%20independence%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E5%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EOnly%20current%20and%20former%20secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20who%20are%20persons%20of%20integrity%2C%20who%20have%20knowledge%20of%20and%20experience%20in%20management%20and%20conduct%20of%20elections%2C%20can%20be%20appointed%20as%20ECs%20or%20CEC.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E6%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3ESearch%20Committee%20consisting%20of%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20and%20two%20other%20Secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20shall%20prepare%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20persons%20for%20consideration%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee%2C%20for%20appointment%20as%20CEC%20and%20ECs.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E7%20(1)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3ESelection%20Committee%20will%20consist%20of%E2%80%94%20(a)%20Prime%20Minister%3B%20(b)%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%3B%20and%20(c)%20a%20Union%20Cabinet%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20PM.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E7(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EAppointment%20of%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20invalid%20merely%20by%20reason%20of%20any%20vacancy%20in%20or%20any%20defect%20in%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E8(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20Selection%20Committee%20may%20also%20consider%20any%20other%20person%20than%20those%20included%20in%20the%20panel%20by%20the%20Search%20Committee.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E9(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20eligible%20for%20re-appointment.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E9(3)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EWhere%20an%20EC%20is%20appointed%20as%20CEC%2C%20his%20term%20of%20office%20shall%20not%20be%20more%20than%20six%20years%20in%20aggregate%20as%20the%20EC%20and%20CEC%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E10(1)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20salary%2C%20allowances%20and%20other%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20shall%20be%20the%20same%20as%20those%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%3A%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E10(5)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EWhere%20the%20CEC%20or%20an%20EC%20had%20retired%20from%20the%20service%20of%20the%20Central%20Govt%20or%20a%20State%20Govt%20prior%20to%20appointment%20as%20such%2C%20the%20aggregate%20period%20for%20which%20the%20encashment%20of%20unutilised%20earned%20leave%20he%20shall%20be%20entitled%20to%2C%20shall%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20maximum%20period%20as%20admissible%20to%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E11(2)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3EThe%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20removed%20except%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20provisions%20contained%20in%20the%20first%20and%20second%20provisos%20respectively%20of%20clause%20(5)%20of%20article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E15%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3ESave%20as%20otherwise%20provided%20in%20this%20Act%2C%20the%20conditions%20of%20service%20relating%20to%20travelling%20allowance%2C%20medical%20facilities%2C%20leave%20travel%20concession%2C%20conveyance%20facilities%2C%20and%20such%20other%20conditions%20of%20service%20as%20are%2C%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20applicable%20to%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20shall%20be%20applicable%20to%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%5Cn%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2266%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22104%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22101%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E9%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20can%20be%20seen%2C%20only%20two%20sections%20are%20likely%20to%20support%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20independence%20whereas%20nine%20will%20work%20towards%20reducing%20it.%20The%20remaining%20sections%20are%20of%20a%20general%20nature%20which%20do%20not%20have%20any%20implications%20for%20the%20institution%E2%80%99s%20independence%2C%20or%20lack%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20while%20the%20Bill%20observes%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20SC%20judgment%20by%20way%20of%20making%20a%20law%2C%20it%20overwhelmingly%2C%20if%20not%20completely%2C%20violates%20the%20spirit%20or%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20judgment.%20As%20the%20court%20observes%20in%20para%20227%20of%20its%20judgment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6it%20was%20intended%20all%20throughout%20that%20appointment%20exclusively%20by%20the%20Executive%20was%20to%20be%20a%20mere%20transient%20or%20stop%20gap%20arrangement%20and%20it%20was%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20a%20law%20made%20by%20the%20Parliament%20taking%20away%20the%20exclusive%20power%20of%20the%20Executive.%20This%20conclusion%20is%20clear%20and%20inevitable%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBarriers%20to%20the%20exercise%20of%20independence%20by%20the%20ECI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20providing%20for%20three%20levels%20of%20barriers%20in%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20government%20has%20tried%20its%20best%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20not%20able%20to%20function%20independently%20under%20any%20circumstances%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EEligibility%20criteria%20for%20EC%20and%20CEC%20appointments%20(Section%205%20of%20the%20Bill)%3A%20Only%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecurrent%20and%20former%20secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20(GoI)%2C%20that%20is%2C%20only%20those%20who%20have%20been%20part%20of%20the%20executive%20for%20long%20are%20to%20be%20considered%20for%20these%20positions.%20How%20independent%20can%20such%20persons%20be%20of%20the%20executive%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20opinion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EProcedure%20for%20shortlisting%20candidates%20(Section%206%20of%20the%20Bill)%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20It%20will%20be%20a%20case%20of%20bureaucrats%20choosing%20bureaucrats%20%E2%80%93%20the%20search%20committee%20comprising%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20and%20two%20other%20secretaries%20to%20the%20GoI%2C%20will%20shortlist%20as%20EC%20and%20CEC%20hopefuls%2C%20persons%20who%20have%20been%20diehard%20members%20of%20the%20executive%20for%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20composition%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20(Section%207(1)%20of%20the%20Bill)%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Whereas%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20had%20suggested%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Bill%20replaces%20the%20non-executive%20element%20of%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20with%20%E2%80%9Ca%20Union%20Cabinet%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20PM.%E2%80%9D%20With%20two%20of%20the%20three%20members%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20hailing%20from%20the%20executive%2C%20how%20can%20anyone%20even%20dream%20of%20an%20Election%20Commission%20acting%20independent%20of%20the%20executive!%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98Umpire%20Cannot%20be%20Subordinate%20to%20Team%20Captain%E2%80%99%3A%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20Raises%20Questions%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Umpire%20Cannot%20be%20Subordinate%20to%20Team%20Captain%E2%80%99%3A%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20Raises%20Questions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeeing%20the%20judgment%20and%20the%20Bill%20in%20a%20larger%20context%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20be%20said%20unambiguously%20that%20while%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20of%20March%2002%2C%202023%2C%20was%20a%20distinct%20step%20forward%20for%20protecting%20democracy%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20proposed%20Bill%20takes%20two%20steps%20backward%20in%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20also%20needs%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20regarding%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20was%20possibly%20influenced%2C%20at%20least%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20by%20the%20prayers%20in%20the%20petitions%20before%20the%20court.%20%5BDisclosure%3A%20an%20organisation%20that%20this%20writer%20is%20associated%20with%2C%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20of%20appointments%20by%20similar%20collegiums%20or%20committees%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20director%2C%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%2C%20central%20information%20commissioners%20and%20chief%20information%20commissioner%2C%20among%20others%20%E2%80%93%20broadly%20shows%20that%20this%20method%20has%20not%20always%20resulted%20in%20the%20best%20possible%20or%20the%20most%20appropriate%20recommendations.%20Maybe%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20break%20new%20ground%20on%20this%20aspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%E2%80%99s%20suggestion%20regarding%20the%20need%20to%20break%20new%20ground%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20distract%20attention%20from%20the%20current%20task%20of%20opposing%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament.%20It%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20damaging%20to%20democracy%20and%20must%20be%20opposed%20at%20all%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20breaking%20new%20ground%20is%20necessary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20criticality%20of%20the%20position%20of%20the%20ECI%2C%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20in%20a%20democracy%20demonstrates%20the%20urgency%20for%20a%20new%20perspective%20on%20the%20issue.%20The%20criticality%20of%20the%20institution%20is%20clearly%20stated%20early%20on%20in%20the%20SC%20judgment%20(para%2041)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Election%20Commissioners%20stand%20on%20a%20%3Cem%3Efar%20higher%20pedestal%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20things%20having%20regard%20to%20the%20relationship%20between%20their%20powers%2C%20%3Cem%3Efunctions%20and%20duties%20and%20the%20upholding%20of%20the%20democratic%20way%20of%20life%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20the%20upkeep%20of%20Rule%20of%20Law%20and%20the%20very%20immutable%20infusion%20of%20life%20into%20the%20grand%20guarantee%20of%20equality%3C%2Fem%3E%20under%20Article%2014%20(emphasis%20added).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20similar%20vein%2C%20the%20SC%20judgment%20also%20describes%20the%20uniqueness%20of%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20which%20provides%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20ECI%20(para%20219)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20clear%20that%20Article%20324%20has%20a%20%3Cem%3Eunique%20background%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20Founding%20Fathers%20clearly%20contemplated%20a%20law%20by%20Parliament%20and%20%3Cem%3Edid%20not%20intend%20the%20executive%20exclusively%20calling%20the%20shots%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20appointments%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20added).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20Bill%20has%20been%20made%20in%20pursuance%20of%20Article%20324(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20says%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20appointment%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%2C%20subject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20in%20that%20behalf%20by%20Parliament%2C%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20context%20that%20the%20court%20examines%20Article%20324(2)%20in%20depth%20in%20a%20section%20of%20the%20judgment%20titled%20%E2%80%98Articles%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20employ%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Csubject%20to%20any%20law%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20made%20by%20Parliament%20as%20contained%20in%20Article%20324.%E2%80%99%20This%20examination%20in%20the%20judgment%2C%20from%20para%2034%20to%20para%2049%2C%20ends%20with%20the%20observation%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20further%20discussion%20is%20needed%20to%20conclude%20that%20Article%20324(2)%20is%20%3Cem%3Eunique%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20its%20setting%20and%20purpose%20(emphasis%20added)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStressing%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20ECs%E2%80%99%20role%2C%20the%20court%20observes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20already%20elaborated%20and%20found%20that%20core%20values%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20including%20democracy%2C%20and%20Rule%20of%20Law%2C%20are%20being%20undermined.%20It%20is%20also%20intricately%20interlinked%20with%20the%20transgression%20of%20Articles%2014%20and%2019.%20Each%20time%2C%20on%20account%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98knave%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%2C%20or%20again%20in%20his%20words%2C%20%E2%80%98a%20person%20under%20the%20thumb%20of%20the%20Executive%E2%80%99%2C%20calls%20the%20shots%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20holding%20the%20elections%2C%20which%20constitutes%20the%20very%20heart%20of%20democracy%2C%20even%20formal%20democracy%2C%20which%20is%20indispensable%20for%20a%20Body%20Polity%20to%20answer%20the%20description%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98democracy%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20(Para%20226).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20contrasts%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20uniqueness%20in%20contrast%20to%20that%20of%20the%20comptroller%20and%20auditor%20general%20of%20India%20while%20comparing%20Articles%20324%20(2)%20and%20148%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20a%20comparison%20of%20both%20the%20Articles%2C%20the%20difference%20is%20stark%20and%20would%20justify%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20contention%20that%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20Members%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20having%20regard%20to%20the%20overwhelming%20importance%20and%20the%20nearly%20infinite%20plenary%20powers%20%5B%2C%5D%20they%20have%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20most%20important%20aspect%20of%20democracy%20itself%2C%20viz.%2C%20the%20holding%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20(para%20228).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20finally%20concludes%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20%3Cem%3Eunique%3C%2Fem%3E%20nature%20of%20the%20provision%20%5BArticle%20324%20(2)%5D%20we%20are%20concerned%20with%20and%20the%20devastating%20effect%20of%20continuing%20to%20leave%20appointments%20in%20sole%20hands%20of%20the%20Executive%20on%20fundamental%20values%2C%20as%20also%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights%E2%80%A6%20(emphasis%20added).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20these%20very%20pointers%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20regarding%20the%20need%20to%20keep%20alive%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20uniqueness%20that%20have%20prompted%20one%20to%20think%20of%20a%20new%20perspective%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20of%20breaking%20new%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20so%E2%80%9D%20new%20ground%20for%20a%20fresh%20perspective%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20may%20surprise%20many%20that%20what%20one%20is%20referring%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20ground%20was%20actually%20explored%20by%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%2C%20Professor%20Shibban%20Lal%20Saxena%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Fdebates%2F15-jun-1949%2F%5C%22%3Emoved%20an%20amendment%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20proposal%20made%20by%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%20The%20significance%20of%20the%20amendment%20is%20such%20that%20it%20deserves%20to%20be%20quoted%20extensively%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMr.%20President%2C%20Sir%2C%20I%20must%20congratulate%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%20on%20moving%20his%20amendment.%20As%20he%20has%20said%2C%20his%20amendment%20really%20carries%20out%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights%20Committee%20and%20in%20fact%20the%20matter%20was%20so%20important%20that%20it%20was%20thought%20at%20one%20time%20that%20it%20should%20be%20included%20in%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights.%20The%20real%20purpose%20is%20that%20the%20fundamental%20right%20of%20adult%20franchise%20should%20not%20only%20be%20guaranteed%20in%20practice.%20He%20has%20explained%20to%20us%20that%20he%20has%20tried%20to%20make%20the%20Election%20Commission%20wholly%20independent%20of%20the%20Executive%20and%20he%20therefore%20hopes%20that%20by%20this%20method%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20franchise%20of%20all%20the%20individuals%20shall%20not%20only%20be%20guaranteed%20but%20that%20it%20shall%20also%20be%20exercised%20in%20a%20proper%20manner%20so%20that%20the%20elected%20People%20will%20represent%20the%20true%20will%20of%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country.%20After%20a%20careful%20study%20of%20his%20amendment%20I%20have%20suggested%20my%20above%20amendments%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20real%20purpose%20of%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20amendment%20in%20full.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20desired%20by%20my%20amendment%20is%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20shall%20be%20completely%20independent%20of%20the%20Executive.%20Of%20course%20it%20shall%20be%20completely%20independent%20of%20the%20provincial%20Executive%20but%20if%20the%20President%20is%20to%20appoint%20this%20Commission%2C%20naturally%20it%20means%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20appoints%20this%20Commission.%20He%20will%20appoint%20the%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20on%20his%20recommendations.%20Now%20this%20does%20not%20ensure%20their%20independence.%20Of%20course%20once%20he%20is%20appointed%20he%20shall%20not%20be%20removable%20except%20by%202%2F3rd%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses.%20That%20is%20certainly%20something%20which%20can%20instil%20independence%20in%20him%2C%20but%20it%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20some%20party%20in%20power%20who%20wants%20to%20win%20the%20next%20election%20may%20appoint%20a%20staunch%20party-man%20as%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner.%20He%20is%20removable%20only%20by%202%2F3rd%20majority%20of%20both%20Houses%20on%20grave%20charges%2C%20which%20means%20that%20he%20is%20almost%20irremovable.%20So%20what%20I%20want%20is%20this%20that%20even%20the%20person%20who%20is%20appointed%20originally%20should%20be%20such%20that%20he%20should%20be%20enjoying%20the%20confidence%20of%20all%20parties%E2%80%93his%20appointment%20should%20be%20confirmed%20not%20only%20by%20majority%20but%20by%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses.%20If%20it%20is%20only%20a%20bare%20majority%20then%20the%20party%20in%20power%20could%20vote%20confidence%20in%20him%20but%20when%20I%20want%202%2F3rd%20majority%20then%20it%20means%20that%20the%20other%20parties%20must%20also%20concur%20in%20the%20appointment%20so%20that%20in%20order%20that%20real%20independence%20of%C2%A0the%20commission%20may%20be%20guaranteed%2C%20in%20order%20that%20everyone%20even%20in%20Opposition%20may%20not%20have%20anything%20to%20say%20against%20the%20Commission%2C%20the%20appointments%20of%20the%20Commissioners%20and%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20must%20be%20by%20the%20President%20but%20the%20names%20proposed%20by%20him%20should%20be%20such%20as%20command%20the%20confidence%20of%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20of%20Legislatures.%20Then%20no%20person%20can%20come%20in%20who%20is%20a%20staunch%20party-man.%20He%20will%20necessarily%20have%20to%20be%20a%20man%20who%20will%20enjoy%20the%20confidence%20of%20not%20only%20one%20party%20but%20also%20of%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Legislature.%20Then%20alone%20he%20can%20get%20a%202%2F3rd%20majority%20in%20support%20of%20his%20appointments.%20I%20therefore%2C%20think%20that%20if%20the%20real%20purpose%20of%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Fundamental%20Rights%20Committee%20is%20to%20be%20carried%20out%2C%20as%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%20proposes%20to%20do%20this%20by%20amendment%2C%20then%20he%20must%20provide%20that%20the%20appointment%20shall%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20be%20by%20the%20president%20subject%20to%20confirmation%20by%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20sitting%20and%20voting%20in%20a%20joint%20session.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20want%20that%20in%20future%2C%20no%20Prime%20Minister%20may%20abuse%20this%20right%2C%20and%20for%20this%20I%20want%20to%20provide%20that%20there%20should%20be%20two-thirds%20majority%20which%20should%20approve%20the%20nomination%20by%20the%20President.%20Of%20course%20there%20is%20danger%20where%20one%20party%20is%20in%20huge%20majority.%20As%20I%20said%20just%20now%20it%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20if%20our%20Prime%20Minister%20wants%2C%20he%20can%20have%20a%20man%20of%20his%20own%20party%2C%20but%20I%20am%20sure%20he%20will%20not%20do%20it.%20Still%20if%20he%20does%20appoint%20a%20party-man%20and%20the%20appointment%20comes%20up%20for%20confirmation%20in%20a%20joint%20session%2C%20even%20a%20small%20opposition%20or%20even%20a%20few%20independent%20members%20can%20down%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20before%20the%20bar%20of%20public%20opinion%20in%20the%20world.%20Because%20we%20are%20in%20a%20majority%20we%20can%20have%20anything%20passed%20only%20theoretically.%20So%20the%20need%20for%20confirmation%20will%20invariably%20ensure%20a%20proper%20choice.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20hope%20this%20majority%20will%20not%20be%20used%20in%20a%20manner%20which%20is%20against%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20nation%20or%20which%20goes%20against%20the%20impartiality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20I%20want%20that%20there%20should%20be%20provision%20in%20the%20Constitution%20so%20that%20even%20in%20the%20future%20if%20some%20Prime%20Minister%20tends%20to%20be%20partial%2C%20he%20should%20not%20be%20able%20to%20be%20so.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20want%20to%20provide%20that%20whenever%20such%20appointment%20is%20made%2C%20the%20person%20appointed%20should%20not%20be%20a%20nominee%20of%20the%20President%20but%20should%20enjoy%20the%20confidence%20of%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20of%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20also%20quotes%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%E2%80%99s%20amendment%20with%20approval%20and%20notes%20that%20the%20amendment%20was%20not%20accepted%20because%20of%20opposition%20from%20some%20other%20members.%20The%20result%20was%20the%20existing%20Article%20324(2)%20saying%20that%20the%20President%20will%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20%E2%80%9Csubject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20in%20that%20behalf%20by%20Parliament.%E2%80%9D%20The%20kind%20of%20Bill%20that%20has%20been%20introduced%20is%20proof%20of%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20foresight!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102430%2Fconstituent-assembly.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102430%2Fconstituent-assembly.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102430%2Fconstituent-assembly-300x194.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671123%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%20meeting%20in%201950.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20can%20be%20seen%20seated%20top-right.%20Photo%3A%20Unknown%20author%2C%20Public%20Domain%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20for%20EC%20and%20CEC%20appointments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Constituent%20Assembly%20member%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20lead%2C%20here%20is%20a%20proposal%20for%20a%20procedure%20to%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20An%20existing%20committee%20of%20parliament%20or%20a%20new%20committee%20formed%20for%20this%20purpose%20to%20propose%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%20for%20appointment%20as%20EC%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20committee%E2%80%99s%20proposals%20would%20then%20be%20placed%20before%20parliament%2C%20requiring%20approval%20by%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20the%20members%20of%20parliament%20present%20and%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Once%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%20are%20approved%20by%20parliament%2C%20the%20same%20committee%20should%20be%20entrusted%20with%20the%20task%20of%20searching%20for%20and%20selecting%20individuals%20for%20the%20position%20of%20ECs%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.1%20The%20committee%20should%20invite%20nominations%20of%20and%20applications%20by%20individuals%20considered%20appropriate%20for%20and%20interested%20in%20being%20appointed%20as%20ECs%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.2%20Out%20of%20the%20nominations%20and%20applications%20received%2C%20the%20suitable%20candidates%20should%20be%20shortlisted%20by%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.3%20The%20interviews%20of%20short-listed%20aspirants%20by%20the%20committee%20should%20be%20conducted%20in%20open%20hearings%2C%20accessible%20for%20viewing%20by%20the%20general%20public%20through%20video-transmission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.4%20After%20the%20hearings%2C%20the%20committee%20should%20select%20individuals%20proposed%20to%20be%20appointed%20as%20ECs%2FCEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20The%20next%20stage%20would%20be%20for%20the%20committee%20to%20send%20its%20recommendations%20to%20parliament%20for%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20The%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20should%20be%20considered%20approved%20by%20parliament%20only%20if%20approved%20by%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20members%20of%20parliament%20present%20and%20voting%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20Once%20approved%20by%20parliament%2C%20the%20recommendations%20should%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20President%20for%20assenting%20to%20the%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20Once%20appointed%2C%20such%20persons%20should%20occupy%20their%20positions%20for%20six%20years%20or%20the%20age%20of%2075%20years%20whichever%20is%20earlier.%20Persons%20above%20the%20age%20of%2069%20years%20should%20not%20be%20appointed%20so%20that%20each%20appointee%20has%20a%20tenure%20of%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20The%20stipulations%20of%20point%207%20should%20apply%20to%20each%20appointment%20independently.%20Every%20EC%20should%20have%20a%20tenure%20of%20six%20years%20and%20every%20CEC%20should%20have%20a%20tenure%20of%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20might%20say%20that%20the%20proposed%20system%20will%20be%20very%20time%20consuming%20and%20may%20even%20term%20it%20impractical.%20This%20may%20well%20be%20true%2C%20given%20the%20way%20parliament%20functions%2C%20or%20does%20not%20function%2C%20these%20days.%20But%20%3Cem%3Eif%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndia%20has%20to%20move%20towards%20a%20really%20functional%20and%20substantive%20democracy%2C%20parliament%20and%20parliamentarians%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20be%20responsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20only%3C%2Fem%3E%20option%20if%20the%20uniqueness%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%20its%20critical%20role%20in%20sustaining%20democracy%20is%20recognised%20and%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJagdeep%20S.%20Chhokar%20is%20a%20concerned%20citizen.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693555257000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-appointments-its-time-to-go-back-to-the-future%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Beyond%20the%20binary%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20disquieting%20new%20Bill%20lies%20a%20fresh%20perspective%20on%20limiting%20executive%20control%20over%20EC%20appointments.%20This%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20perspective%20goes%20back%20to%20prescient%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-appointments-its-time-to-go-back-to-the-future%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fugitive%20stepmother%20of%2010-year-old%20girl%20who%20was%20found%20dead%20urged%20to%20hand%20herself%20in%20by%20relative%22%2C%22content%22%3